      "locked": false,
      "text": "Scenario\n\nYou are responsible for a multi-tenant job execution platform used by internal product teams to run high-cost analytical jobs (ML training, backfills, regulatory\nreports).\n\nRecently:\n        •        A finance audit flagged unbounded cost overruns\n        •        A production incident revealed that control-plane outages canceled active jobs\n        •        Several teams accused the platform of silently duplicating work\n\nLeadership mandate:\n\n“We must guarantee cost safety, execution correctness, and operational independence — without killing developer velocity.”\n\n⸻\n\nBusiness Context (Why this exists)\n        •        The platform executes billions of dollars of compute annually\n        •        Jobs may run minutes to days\n        •        Some jobs are regulatory or revenue-critical\n        •        Tenants do not trust each other\n        •        CFO demands provable budget enforcement\n        •        SRE demands clear blast-radius containment\n\n⸻\n\nHard Constraints (Non-Negotiable)\n        •        Multi-tenant (hundreds of tenants, wildly different spend profiles)\n        •        Budgets are real money — overspend requires executive approval\n        •        Jobs must survive control-plane outages\n        •        Duplicate execution is unacceptable\n        •        Latency is secondary to correctness\n        •        You may degrade performance, but not violate invariants",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Scenario\n\nYou are responsible for a multi-tenant job execution platform used by internal product teams to run high-cost analytical jobs (ML training, backfills, regulatory reports).\n\nRecently:\n        •        A finance audit flagged unbounded cost overruns\n        •        A production incident revealed that control-plane outages canceled active jobs\n        •        Several teams accused the platform of silently duplicating work\n\nLeadership mandate:\n\n“We must guarantee cost safety, execution correctness, and operational independence — without killing developer velocity.”\n\n⸻\n\nBusiness Context (Why this exists)\n        •        The platform executes billions of dollars of compute annually\n        •        Jobs may run minutes to days\n        •        Some jobs are regulatory or revenue-critical\n        •        Tenants do not trust each other\n        •        CFO demands provable budget enforcement\n        •        SRE demands clear blast-radius containment\n\n⸻\n\nHard Constraints (Non-Negotiable)\n        •        Multi-tenant (hundreds of tenants, wildly different spend profiles)\n        •        Budgets are real money — overspend requires executive approval\n        •        Jobs must survive control-plane outages\n        •        Duplicate execution is unacceptable\n        •        Latency is secondary to correctness\n        •        You may degrade performance, but not violate invariants",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
